article.headline: East Carolina 87, Radford 50
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Derrick Wiley scored a game-high 26 points and East Carolina downed Radford 87-50 on Tuesday night. Wiley converted 10 of 18 shots from the field and had six rebounds. Gabriel Mikulas pitched in 15 points for the Pirates (8-1). East Carolina trailed 13-12 early but Wiley responded with back-to-back 3-pointers to start a 20-6 run. The Pirates led 34-21 at halftime. East Carolina shot 69 percent from the field in the second half, outscoring the Highlanders (4-6) by 24 in the second half. Erroyl Bing had 10 and Mike Cook had 10 points, seven rebounds and five assists off the bench for the Pirates. Whit Holcomb-Faye had 13 points, nine rebounds and five assists for Radford, which shot 30 percent from the field. Kyle Zaharias finished with 10. The Highlanders went 1-of-14 from 3-point range.
